# Infrastructure Handbook

A concise handbook with step-by-step guides for server setup, Linux configurations, and DevOps essentials simplifying infrastructure management and deployments.

## Contents

This repository contains practical guides and documentation for common infrastructure tasks:

- [Fail2Ban Installation Guide](fail2ban_installation_guide.md) - Complete guide for installing and configuring Fail2Ban on Oracle Linux 7.9 with automatic IP blocking after failed authentication attempts

- [Installing Docker CE on Oracle Linux 7.9](installing_docker_ce_on_oracle_linux_7.9.md) - Step-by-step instructions for Docker Community Edition installation and setup

## Purpose

This handbook serves as a reference collection for:

- Server security hardening
- Container orchestration setup
- Linux system configurations
- DevOps automation workflows
- Infrastructure best practices

## Usage

Each guide is self-contained and can be followed independently. All configurations are tested on Linux.

## Contributing

Feel free to submit issues or pull requests to improve existing guides or add new infrastructure documentation.

